description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a motivated, confident, compassionate and enthusiastic individual to join our excellent team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If making a difference to our patient’s matters to you then this role may be exactly what you are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is an expectation that you will rotate through each of the 3 hub teams, developing your knowledge base, leadership, assessment and negotiation skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a generic assessor you will need to be a forward thinking, autonomous practitioner, flexible, willing to develop interchangeable skills across professional boundaries, be knowledgeable on a range of conditions, their treatment and potential for deterioration. Enhanced training will be provided to assist with generic skills development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work in a fast moving clinical environment, possess excellent communication skills, and have previous experience of discharge planning. Effective decision making, the ability to manage risk effectively in complex discharges and demonstrating leadership qualities are integral to this post. This level of experience is normally associated with at extensive post registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team in reach into the emergency department, the assessment units and remain involved with a patients journey through to a base ward for the first 72 hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The common purpose of the team is to improve the patient experience by facilitating a safe and timely transfer of care to the appropriate setting. You will achieve this by commencing the assessment process, and completing any necessary onward referrals. Our philosophy is ‘home first’ where the assessment process can continue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are inviting people with community or hospital experience to apply for this post with a professional background of nursing or therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time of forging links with our community colleagues, and embracing the current developments and projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Bye, Operational Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email addressl.bye@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0114 3078642&lt;/p&gt;
